row.column:
With the wide variety of Acumatica ERP reports related to accounts payable, you can promptly get vital information, analyze financial data by various criteria, and review transactions efficiently. Some reports have both a standard version and a multi-currency (MC) version. If a report contains data links, you can easily drill down from the report to any supporting details.((({S:Hint}
A report includes only the objects or entities that the user running the report is authorized to access, based on the user&rsquo;s roles and membership in restriction groups. 
)))
 All accounts payable reports can be generated in different formats, including PDFs, and can be printed or sent by email. For more information about reports, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports].{br}

Each of the topics of this chapter provides reference information about a particular Acumatica ERP report, including details about the applicable report parameters you can use to select the exact data you want to view and analyze.

Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=AP653000|AP653000])((({S:Hint}This report is available only if the ''1099 Reporting'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. ))) This report displays the 1099-MISC (Miscellaneous) form for the selected 1099 year. {br}
If the amount in Box 9 exceeds the minimum reporting amount specified in the '''Minimum Report Amount''' box on the '''1099 Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_10_10_00|Accounts Payable Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=AP101000|AP101000]) form, the report displays ''X'' in this box.[anchor|#_7d7cbd09-0b65-4918-b520-2e6f20108695]{br}
See below for a description of each parameter on the '''Report Parameters''' tab of the report form. For more information about using other elements on the report form, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports]. ==Report Parameters== On the '''Report Parameters''' tab, you use the following parameters to select the information to be displayed on the report: *'''Company''': The company for which you want to view information. By default, the current company is selected. This box is available only if the ''Multi-Branch Support'' feature is enabled in your system on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. *'''1099 Year''': The 1099 year for which the 1099-MISC form will be displayed. Select the year from the list, which contains both open and closed 1099 years. *'''NEC (Box 7)''': The way the report will be generated with regard to non-employee compensation (NEC) in box 7. Select one of the following options: **''All Boxes'' (default): The system generates the report for all vendors with all boxes displayed; the box 7 amounts are not given special consideration. **''Only Box 7'': The report will include only box 7 data (and thus only vendors for which this box is filled in). Even if multiple boxes are filled in for a vendor, if this option is selected, only the box 7 amounts for the vendor will be shown in the report. **''Except Box 7'': The report will include all boxes data except box 7. If multiple boxes are filled in for a vendor, if this option is selected, all these boxes except box 7 will be shown in the report.

Form ID:  ([~/?ScreenId=AP642000|AP642000]){br}

This report can be used to print check stubs. {br}

To use this report, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CA_20_40_00|Payment Methods] ([~/?ScreenId=CA204000|CA204000]) form, select the '''Print Remittance Report''' check box and select this report as the '''Remittance Report'''. Check stubs will be printed for the specified payment method and cash account for all printed checks, starting with the check with the selected number. For details on modifying the report, see the [HelpRoot_ReportingTools\ReportDesigner_Main| Acumatica Report                         Designer Guide].[anchor|#_da53c6bb-c142-4717-8268-398400cc125c]{br}

See below for a description of each parameter on the '''Report Parameters''' tab of the report form. For more information about using other elements on the report form, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports].
==Report Parameters==
On the '''Report Parameters''' tab, you use the following parameters to select the information to be displayed on the report: 
*'''Cash Account''': A cash account associated with a payment method that requires printing of checks.
*'''Payment Method''': A payment method that requires printing of checks.
*'''From Check Number''': The starting number of checks for which stubs should be printed.
*'''To Check Number''': The ending number of checks for which stubs should be printed.

Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=AP631500|AP631500]){br}
This report displays the list of vendors with outstanding balances. The overdue balances are displayed in the '''Past Due''' column, while the balances that are not overdue are arranged by days outstanding. The report can be shown in summary format or in detailed format with the documents that created the balance. The amounts are shown in the base currency. [anchor|#_8a250fa7-c14e-4f0b-ac70-6a5359e788fc]{br}
See below for a description of each parameter on the '''Report Parameters''' tab of the report form. For more information about using other elements on the report form, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports]. ==Report Parameters== On the '''Report Parameters''' tab, you use the following parameters to select the information to be displayed on the report: *'''Report Format''': The format of the report. Select one of the following options: **''Detailed'' (default): To view outstanding documents on the selected aging date **''Summary'': To view outstanding balances on the selected aging date *'''Company''': The company for which you want to view information. You can select a company or make no selection to view information about all companies. *:By default, the company to which you are signed in is selected. *'''Branch''': The branch for which you want to view information. You can select a branch or make no selection to view information about all branches. *:By default, the current branch is selected. *:This box appears on the form only if the ''Multi-Branch Support'' feature is enabled in your system on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. *'''Vendor Class''': The vendor class whose vendors will be included in the report. Select a vendor class from the list of vendor classes, or make no selection to view information about all classes. *'''Vendor''': The vendor the report will cover. Select a vendor from the list of active vendors, or make no selection to view information about all vendors. *'''Aging Date''': The date the system will use to calculate the aging categories for the documents; you must select a date. *:((({S:Hint}If some documents do not have a due date specified, the system sets the due date for these documents to the '''Aging Date''' value. The balances of the documents that are due on the aging date of the report are included in the first aging period of the report. )))

Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=AP631000|AP631000]){br}
This report lists the vendors with past due balances. The balances that are not overdue are displayed in the '''Current''' column of the report. The overdue balances are broken down by days past due, based on the aging periods defined on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_10_10_00|Accounts Payable Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=AP101000|AP101000]) form. All the amounts are shown in the base currency. [anchor|#_953574dd-3db1-4bad-ac80-98aaeba29d3b]{br}
See below for a description of each parameter on the '''Report Parameters''' tab of the report form. For more information about using other elements on the report form, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports]. ==Report Parameters== On the '''Report Parameters''' tab, you use the following parameters to select the information to be displayed on the report: *'''Report Format''': The format of the report. Select one of the following options: **''Summary'': To view past due balances on the selected aging date **''Detailed'' (default): To view past due documents and their balances on the selected aging date **''Detailed with Retainage'': To view past due documents and their unreleased retainage on the selected aging date **:((({S:Hint}This format is available only if the ''Retainage Support'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. ))) *'''Company''': The company for which past due balances will be displayed. You can select a company or make no selection to view information about all companies in the tenant. *:By default, the current company is selected. *'''Branch''': The branch for which past due balances will be displayed. You can select a branch or make no selection to view information about all branches. *:By default, the current branch is selected. *:This box appears on the form only if the ''Multi-Branch Support'' feature is enabled in your system on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. *'''Vendor Class''': The vendor class for which past due balances will be listed. Select a vendor class from the list of vendor classes, or make no selection to view information about all classes. *'''Vendor''': The vendor the report will cover. Select a vendor from the list of active vendors, or make no selection to view information about all vendors. *'''Aging Date''': The date the system will use when calculating the aging categories for the documents. *:By default, the current business date is selected. *:((({S:Hint}If some documents do not have a due date specified, the system sets the due date for these documents to the '''Aging Date''' value. The balances of these documents are included in the '''Current''' column of the report. )))

Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=AP631100|AP631100]){br}
This form is available only if the ''Multi-Currency Accounting'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. {br}
This multi-currency report lists the vendors with past due balances. The balances that are not overdue are displayed in the '''Current''' column of the report. The overdue balances are broken down by days past due, based on the aging periods defined on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_10_10_00|Accounts Payable Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=AP101000|AP101000]) form. The amounts are shown in the currencies of the documents and in the base currency. [anchor|#_2864d0a7-e068-4272-b0ab-3be9df25fef8]{br}
See below for a description of each parameter on the '''Report Parameters''' tab of the report form. For more information about using other elements on the report form, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports]. ==Report Parameters== On the '''Report Parameters''' tab, you use the following parameters to select the information to be displayed on the report: *'''Report Format''': The format of the report. Select one of the following options: **''Detailed'' (default): To view outstanding customer documents **''Summary'': To view outstanding customer balances *'''Company''': The company for which you want to view information. You can select a company or make no selection to view information about all companies. *:By default, the company to which you are signed in is selected. *'''Branch''': The branch for which past due balances will be displayed. You can select a branch or make no selection to view information about all branches. *:By default, the current branch is selected. *:This box appears on the form only if the ''Multi-Branch Support'' feature is enabled in your system on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. *'''Vendor Class''': The vendor class whose balances will be included in the report. Select a vendor class from the list of vendor classes, or make no selection to view information about all classes. *'''Vendor''': The vendor the report will cover. Select a vendor from the list of active vendors, or make no selection to view information about all vendors. *'''Aging Date''': The date the system will use when calculating the aging categories for the documents. *:By default, the current business date is selected. *:((({S:Hint}If some documents do not have a due date specified, the system sets the due date for these documents to the '''Aging Date''' value. The balances of these documents are included in the '''Current''' column of the report. )))

Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=AP630500|AP630500]){br}
This report displays the list of vendors with past due balances. The balances are arranged by days past due on the last day of the specified period. All the amounts are shown in the base currency. [anchor|#_27db1b16-124e-4369-bb68-17ff6d35b760]{br}
See below for a description of each parameter on the '''Report Parameters''' tab of the report form. For more information about using other elements on the report form, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports]. ==Report Parameters== On the '''Report Parameters''' tab, you use the following parameters to select the information to be displayed on the report: *'''Report Format''': The format of the report. Select one of the following options: **''Detailed'' (default): To view past due documents on the last day of the selected period **''Summary'': To view past due balances on the last day of the selected period *'''Company''': The company for which you want to view information. You can select a company or make no selection to view information about all companies. *:By default, the company to which you are signed in is selected. *'''Branch''': The branch for which information will be displayed. You can select a branch or make no selection to view information about all branches. *:By default, the current branch is selected. *:This box appears on the form only if the ''Multi-Branch Support'' feature is enabled in your system on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. *'''Financial Period''': The financial period the system will use to calculate the aging categories for the documents. By default, the current business period is selected. *'''Vendor Class''': The vendor class for which you want to view information. Select a vendor class, or make no selection to view information about all classes. *'''Use Master Calendar''': A check box that you select to use the financial period from the master calendar. If the check box is cleared, the report will show data for the company calendar. *:This check box appears on the form only if the ''Multiple Calendar Support'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form. *:For details on running consolidated reports and inquiries, see [HelpRoot_Financials\GL__CON_Consolidated_Reports_for_Companies_with_Different_Calendars|Consolidated Reports for Companies with Different Calendars].

Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=AP632000|AP632000]){br}
This report displays the balances of the AP accounts and activities on the accounts for the selected period. Documents are grouped by account, subaccount, and vendor. [anchor|#_76f4e666-13e3-42e4-b648-e24017309bfa]{br}
See below for a description of each parameter on the '''Report Parameters''' tab of the report form. For more information about using other elements on the report form, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports]. ==Report Parameters== On the '''Report Parameters ''' tab, you use the following parameters to select the information to be displayed on the report: *'''Report Format''': An indicator of the information to be shown in the report. Select one of the following options: **''Account Summary'': To view each vendor&rsquo;s total on documents that are open at the end of the reporting period, grouped by AP account and subaccount. **''Vendor Summary'': To view account documents total split by documents total of the of the vendors. **''Open Documents'': To view the list of the documents that are open at the end of the reporting period grouped by AP account, subaccount, and vendor account. **''Open + Current Period'': To view documents that are open at the end of the reporting period along with documents posted or closed during the reporting period, grouped by AP account, subaccount, and vendor account. *'''Company''': The company for which you want to view information. You can select a company or make no selection to view information about all companies. *:By default, the company to which you are signed in is selected. *'''Branch''': The branch for which you want to view information. You can select a branch or make no selection to view information about all branches. *:By default, the current branch is selected. *:This box appears on the form only if the ''Multi-Branch Support'' feature is enabled in your system on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. *'''Financial Period''': The financial period for which balances will be shown. You must select a financial period from the list of periods, which contains all the periods (including the closed ones). *'''Include Applications''': A check box you select to include applied documents. That is, for each vendor, outgoing payments that were applied against vendor bills are listed. *'''Use Master Calendar''': A check box that you select to use the financial period from the master calendar. If the check box is cleared, the report will show data for the company calendar. *:This check box appears on the form only if the ''Multiple Calendar Support'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form. *:For details on running consolidated reports and inquiries, see [HelpRoot_Financials\GL__CON_Consolidated_Reports_for_Companies_with_Different_Calendars|Consolidated Reports for Companies with Different Calendars].

Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=AP632500|AP632500]){br}
This report displays the vendor balances for each account related to the vendor in the financial period you specify. You can control which documents you view and whether they are matched against payments. All the amounts are shown in the base currency. [anchor|#_8df3e2c2-113f-4c66-a36d-9f5e3bc6d1ed]{br}
See below for a description of each parameter on the '''Report Parameters''' tab of the report form. For more information about using other elements on the report form, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports]. ==Report Parameters== On the '''Report Parameters ''' tab, you use the following parameters to select the information to be displayed on the report: *'''Report Format''': An indicator of the information to be shown in the report. Select one of the following options: **''Account Summary'': To view each vendor&rsquo;s total on documents that are open at the end of the reporting period, grouped by AP account and subaccount. **''Open Documents'': To view the list of the documents that are open at the end of the reporting period. **''Open + Current Period'': To view the documents that are open at the end of the reporting period, along with the documents posted or closed during the reporting period. **''All Documents (Vendor Required)'': To view the documents that have been posted before the end of the reporting period. You must specify a vendor if you select this option. *'''Company''': The company for which you want to view information. You can select a company or make no selection to view information about all companies. *:By default, the company to which you are signed in is selected. *'''Branch''': The branch for which you want to view information. You can select a branch or make no selection to view information about all branches. *:By default, the current branch is selected. *:This box appears on the form only if the ''Multi-Branch Support'' feature is enabled in your system on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. *'''Financial Period''': The financial period for which information will be displayed. You must select a financial period from the list of periods, which contains all the periods (including the closed ones). *:By default, the current financial period is used. *'''Vendor''': The vendor whose balances will be included in the report. Either select a vendor from the list of active vendors or make no selection to view information about all vendors. *'''Include Applications''': A check box that you select to include payment application in the report. *'''Use Master Calendar''': A check box that you select to use the financial period from the master calendar. If the check box is cleared, the report will use the financial period of the company calendar. *:This check box appears on the form only if the ''Multiple Calendar Support'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form. *:For details on running consolidated reports and inquiries, see [HelpRoot_Financials\GL__CON_Consolidated_Reports_for_Companies_with_Different_Calendars|Consolidated Reports for Companies with Different Calendars].

Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=AP620500|AP620500]){br}
This report lists AP transactions generated during the financial period or range of periods you specify. Transactions are listed by their date and shown with batch control totals in the base currency. [anchor|#_5ab06914-13ba-4448-b7e0-73c23008d5eb]{br}
See below for a description of each parameter on the '''Report Parameters''' tab of the report form. For more information about using other elements on the report form, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports]. ==Report Parameters== On the '''Report Parameters''' tab, you use the following parameters to select the information to be displayed on the report:[anchor|#ul_exr_fds_fq] *'''Company''': The company for which you want to view information. You can select a company or make no selection to view information about all companies. *:By default, the company to which you are signed in is selected. *'''Branch''': The branch for which you want to view information. You can select a branch or make no selection to view information about all branches. *:By default, the current branch is selected. *:This box appears on the form only if the ''Multi-Branch Support'' feature is enabled in your system on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. *'''Ledger''': The ledger to be reported on. You must select a ledger. *'''From Period''': The first financial period of the period range the report will cover. You must select a period. *:By default, the current financial period is used. *'''To Period''': The last financial period of the period range the report will cover. You must select a period. *:By default, the current financial period is used. *'''Created By''': The user who created the batches whose information you want to view. *'''Last Modified By''': The user who last modified the batches whose information you want to view. *'''Include Unposted Transactions''': A check box that indicates (if selected) that information about unposted transactions will be included in the report. This setting takes effect if the '''Automatically Post on Release''' check box is cleared on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_10_10_00|Accounts Payable Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=AP101000|AP101000]) form.

