With the Acumatica ERP reports related to equipment management, you can promptly get detailed information about service contracts and equipment. You can also analyze the contract-related and equipment-related data by various criteria, and track service operations for different customers and locations. If a report contains data links, you can easily drill down from the report to any supporting details.((({S:Hint}
A report includes only the objects or entities that the user running the report is authorized to access, based on the user&rsquo;s roles and membership in restriction groups. 
)))
 All equipment management reports can be generated in different formats, including PDFs, and can be printed or sent by email. For more information about reports, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports].{br}

Each of the topics of this chapter provides reference information about a particular Acumatica ERP report, including details about the applicable report parameters you can use to select the exact data you want to view and analyze.

Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=FS659500|FS659500]){br}
This report displays information about all inventory items (services, non-stock items, and stock items) included in each appointment, grouped by target equipment. You can filter data by any of the following: a customer, a customer location, and a contract target equipment. [anchor|#_846fa2ca-4355-45f1-89f2-9b3a78bf12db]{br}
See below for a description of each parameter on the '''Report Parameters''' tab of the report form. For more information about using other elements on the report form, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports]. ==Report Parameters== On the '''Report Parameters''' tab, you use the following parameters to select the information to be displayed on the report: [anchor|#_5bb0d61b-baa1-4528-8a18-97b79faf1c5b] *'''Report Format''': The report format, which in this case indicates the level of detail of data in the report to be generated. The following options are available: **''Detailed'' (default): The report shows details on target equipment for each inventory item. **''Summary'': The report shows summary information for each inventory item. *'''Start Date''': The start date for which you want to view information. *'''End Date''': The end date for which you want to view information. By default, the current business date is selected. *'''Customer''': The customer for which you want to view data. Leave the box blank to view information on all customers. *'''Location''': The customer location for which you want to view data. Leave the box blank to view information on all customer locations. *'''Target Equipment''': The target equipment for which you want to view data. Leave the box blank to view information on all target equipment.

Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=FS658000|FS658000]){br}
This report displays information about all inventory items (services, non-stock items, and stock items) included in each appointment, grouped by contract. You can filter data by any of the following: a customer, a customer location, a service contract, and a contract schedule. [anchor|#_eabf4efc-11c2-4a4f-ab73-5a313dd74994]{br}
See below for a description of each parameter on the '''Report Parameters''' tab of the report form. For more information about using other elements on the report form, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports]. ==Report Parameters== On the '''Report Parameters''' tab, you use the following parameters to select the information to be displayed on the report: [anchor|#_5bb0d61b-baa1-4528-8a18-97b79faf1c5b] *'''Report Format''': The report format, which in this case indicates the level of detail of data in the report to be generated. The following options are available: **''Detailed'' (default): The report shows details on each inventory item. **''Summary'': The report shows summary information for each inventory item, such as estimated and actual duration of services, quantity of items, and amount. *'''Start Date''': The start date for which you want to view information. *'''End Date''': The end date for which you want to view information. By default, the current business date is selected. *'''Customer''': The customer for which you want to view data. Leave the box blank to view information on all customers. *'''Location''': The customer location for which you want to view data. Leave the box blank to view information on all customer locations. *'''Service Contract ID''': The identifier of the service contract for which you want to view data. Leave the box blank to view information on all service contracts. *'''Schedule ID''': The identifier of the schedule for which you want to view data. Leave the box blank to view information on all service contract schedules. *'''Target Equipment Details''': A check box that indicates (if selected) that report will display target equipment information.

