With the wide variety of Acumatica ERP reports related to service management, you can promptly get detailed information about appointments and service orders. You can also analyze the data by various criteria, and track service operations for different customers and locations. If a report contains data links, you can easily drill down from the report to any supporting details. ((({S:Hint}
A report includes only the objects or entities that the user running the report is authorized to access, based on the user&rsquo;s roles and membership in restriction groups. 
)))
 All service management reports can be generated in different formats, including PDF and HTML, and can be printed or sent by email. For more information about reports, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports].{br}

Each of the topics of this chapter provides reference information about a particular Acumatica ERP report, including details about the applicable report parameters you can use to select the exact data you want to view and analyze.

Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=FS642000|FS642000]){br}
By using this report, you can display the selected appointment as a ready-to-print document. The document provides the company information (in the top left), contact information, customer information, included services (and their quantities and prices), inventory item information, information about the staff members performing the services, and the total price of the appointment.[anchor|#_1f15c348-cfc2-4a41-bf84-4a3bbbbbc70e]{br}
See below for a description of each parameter on the '''Report Parameters''' tab of the report form. For more information about using other elements on the report form, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports]. ==Report-Specific Parameters== On the '''Report Parameters''' tab, you use the following parameters to select the data to be displayed on the report: [anchor|#_a4b54e90-4675-41a2-8976-755c72f78620] *'''Service Order Type''': The service order type related to the appointment you want to display. You must specify the type. *'''Appointment Number''': The number of the appointment you want to display. You must specify the number of the appointment.

Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=FS653000|FS653000]){br}
This report displays information about all inventory items (services, non-stock items, and stock items) included in each appointment, grouped by customer. You can select appointments by customer, customer location, and inventory item. [anchor|#_9ee01ab7-2a46-4b3e-8c8f-db15b7f15c37]{br}
See below for a description of each parameter on the '''Report Parameters''' tab of the report form. For more information about using other elements on the report form, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports]. ==Report Parameters== On the '''Report Parameters ''' tab, you use the following parameters to select the data to be displayed on the report: [anchor|#_5bb0d61b-baa1-4528-8a18-97b79faf1c5b] *'''Report Format''': The report format, which in this case indicates the level of detail of data in the report to be generated. The following options are available: **''Detailed'' (default): The report shows details on each inventory item. **''Summary'': The report shows summary appointment information for each customer, such as estimated and actual duration of services, quantity of items, and amount. *'''Start Date''': The start date for which you want to view information. *'''End Date''': The end date for which you want to view information. By default, the current business date is selected. *'''Customer''': The customer for which you want to view data. Leave the box blank to view information on all customers. *'''Location''': The customer location for which you want to view data. Leave the box blank to view information on all customer locations. *'''Inventory''': The service, non-stock item, or stock item for which you want to view data. Leave the box blank to view information on all inventory items. *'''Target Equipment Details''': A check box that indicates (if selected) that report will display target equipment information.

