Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=TX631000|TX631000]){br}
This report lists the documents that have a value-added tax (VAT) balance pending recognition at the end of the selected financial period. (For details about the recognition of pending VAT, see [HelpRoot_Financials\TX__con_Recognition_of_Pending_VAT|Recognition of Pending VAT].){br}
By using this report, you can reconcile the documents that have unrecognized VAT amounts with the balances of the Pending Tax Payable and Pending Tax Claimable accounts.[anchor|#_175506ed-c7a7-48c3-bb59-6ba054ace690]{br}
See below for a description of each parameter on the '''Report Parameters''' tab of the report form. For more information about using other elements on the report form, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports]. ==Report Parameters== On the '''Report Parameters ''' tab, you use the following parameters to select the data to be displayed on the report: [anchor|#ul_h1q_hbl_sx] *'''Report Format''': The format, which in this case defines which taxes the report will cover. The following options are available: **''Output VAT'': The report will include documents that are subject to pending VAT of the ''Output'' reporting group—that is, VAT that must be reported to a tax agency. **''Input VAT'': The report will include documents that are subject to pending VAT of the ''Input'' reporting group—that is, the taxes that can be claimed from a tax agency. *'''Company''': The company for which the report will be prepared. *:By default, the current company is selected. *'''Branch''': The branch for which the report should be prepared. To include all documents with VAT pending recognition in the report, leave this box empty. *:This box is available only if the ''Multi-Branch Support'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, and only if the company selected in the '''Company''' box has the ''With Branches Requiring Balancing'' type and the '''File Taxes by Branches''' check box selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_15_00|Companies] ([~/?ScreenId=CS101500|CS101500]) form. *'''Financial Period''': The tax period that the report should cover. To include all documents with a VAT balance pending recognition, clear this box. *:By default, the period of the current business date is used. *'''Account''': The account whose tax amounts pending recognition should be included in the report. Accounts that hold tax amounts pending recognition are those specified for value-added taxes in the '''Pending Tax Payable Account''' or '''Pending Tax Claimable Account''' box on the '''GL Accounts''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\TX_20_50_00|Taxes] ([~/?ScreenId=TX205000|TX205000]) form. Leave this box blank to view VAT amounts pending recognition for all accounts. *'''Subaccount''': The subaccount whose VAT amounts pending recognition should be included in the report. Subaccounts that hold tax amounts pending recognition are those specified for value-added taxes in the '''Pending Tax Payable Subaccount''' or '''Pending Tax Claimable Subaccount''' box on the '''GL Accounts''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\TX_20_50_00|Taxes] form. Leave this box blank to view VAT amounts pending recognition for all subaccounts. *:This box is available only if the ''Subaccounts'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form.

The Acumatica ERP reports related to user security provide information that can be useful for employees who manage users, roles, and access rights to system objects. You can use these reports for analyzing, optimizing, and restructuring user accounts, user roles, and access rights. If a report contains data links, you can easily drill down from the report to any supporting details. ((({S:Hint}
A report includes only the objects or entities that the user running the report is authorized to access, based on the user&rsquo;s roles and membership in restriction groups. 
)))
 All reports related to user security can be generated in different formats, including PDF and HTML, and can be printed or sent by email. For more information about reports, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports].{br}

Each of the topics of this chapter provides reference information about a particular Acumatica ERP report, including details about the applicable report parameters you can use to select the exact data you want to view and analyze.

row.Content:
Form ID:  ([~/?ScreenId=SM651500|SM651500]){br}

This report lists the roles available in the system and their access rights to system forms. Only those forms for which access rights were set up explicitly at the form, module, or suite level are displayed in the report.[anchor|#_eb36b889-2b66-4c46-a2ef-c046eeabc24f]{br}

The report has no report-specific parameters. For more information about using other elements on the report form, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports].

Form ID:  ([~/?ScreenId=SM651700|SM651700]){br}

This report lists all system forms with user roles for which access rights to the form have been set up explicitly at the form, module, or suite level. Each role&rsquo;s level of access rights to the form is displayed.[anchor|#_61c7eb39-f7f4-4c02-95a4-a18ad99e8686]{br}

The report has no report-specific parameters. For more information about using other elements on the report form, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports].

row.column:
Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=SM651000|SM651000]){br}
This report lists the roles available in the system and the user accounts assigned to each role. The report can be created in a summary or detailed format. [anchor|#_4b488a2f-db31-4874-88be-1bd4186052ca]{br}
See below for a description of each parameter on the '''Report Parameters''' tab of the report form. For more information about using other elements on the report form, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports]. ==Report Parameters== On the '''Report Parameters ''' tab, use the following parameter to select the information to be displayed on the report: *'''Format''': The format in which you want to generate the report. Select one of the following options: **''Detailed'': Displays the list of roles, with the description of each role and the total number of users with the role assigned. For each role, lists the users with the role assigned and the basic information, including email address, for each user. **''Summary'': Displays the list of roles, with the description of each role and the total number of users who have the role assigned.

Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=SM650500|SM650500]){br}
This report, which can be created in a summary or detailed format, displays the existing user accounts and their key properties. [anchor|#_5e8a0d4b-a0a8-482d-95f2-1b62afb15bff]{br}
See below for a description of each parameter on the '''Report Parameters''' tab of the report form. For more information about using other elements on the report form, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Report_Processing_Options|Reports]. ==Report Parameters== On the '''Report Parameters ''' tab, use the following parameter to select the information to be displayed on the report: *'''Format''': The format in which you want to generate the report. Select one of the following options: **''Detailed'': Displays the complete list of user accounts with key account properties (such as first and last name, and password security options). For each account, the report lists the roles assigned to the account. **''Summary'': Displays the complete list of user accounts with key account properties (such as first and last name, and password security options).
